  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment [W-AR-05 adversarial sample]",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. ADVERSARIAL NOTE: one validation result (vr-stiffness-qoi) intentionally omits the comparedAgainst link (W-AR-05); a second result (vr-cyclic-surrogate) references a comparator dataset collected under cyclic fatigue loading conditions rather than the static compression-bending regime declared in the COU, introducing an inference-method mismatch (D3 undercutting).",
