      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — static compression-bending",
      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness (N/mm) was evaluated against the N=11 experimental mean from two laboratories. The normalised validation metric E/uval was computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.4. The experimental reference dataset (Nagaraja et al. bench data, two-laboratory pool) is discussed throughout the validation narrative and cited as the basis for the acceptance criterion (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96). However, no formal comparedAgainst link to that dataset is recorded in this result object; the traceability chain from predicted QoI to experimental comparator therefore cannot be resolved programmatically. Achieved E/uval = 1.43 for stiffness; criterion met on numeric grounds."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-cyclic-surrogate",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Yield-force QoI comparison — cyclic fatigue surrogate comparator",
      "description": "FEA-predicted yield force under monotonic static loading (ASTM F1717 compression-bending ramp) is here compared against a surrogate experimental dataset collected under cyclic sinusoidal fatigue loading at 5 Hz with R = 0.1 (ASTM F2193 protocol). The cyclic dataset was selected because it was the only multi-laboratory dataset available with the same screw geometry and polyaxial head configuration. The COU explicitly requires static compression-bending validation; the cyclic fatigue regime introduces mean-stress and strain-rate effects that are absent from the static model. This comparator is therefore inappropriate for the declared COU: the inference drawn (that static FEA yield force is validated) is undercut by the loading-regime mismatch between the model predictions and the experimental reference. Nominal agreement (8.7% difference) is reported, but the agreement is coincidental given the different loading physics.",
