    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted at Medium assurance level. Eleven of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. Two factors fall below required level: Test conditions (achieved 2, required 3) due to single loading angle; Relevance of validation activities to COU (achieved 2, required 3) due to use of a cyclic fatigue comparator for the yield-force QoI in a static compression-bending COU. Both gaps are documented and accepted by the project team on the basis that (a) the 5° angle is the standard regulatory endpoint and (b) nominal numerical agreement is within the 10% acceptance bound. The stiffness QoI validation result lacks a comparedAgainst link; traceability is maintained through narrative citation only. Decision accepted with recommendation to resolve both open traceability issues in the next model revision.",
